                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the word mǝʿrāf (“chapter”) and the
                           chapter numbers; two lines on the incipit page (fol. 3r) of the
                           Introduction; some lines on the incipit page of each Gospel, divided into
                           several groups, alternating with black lines: 6 lines for the Gospels of
                           Matthew and John, 4 lines for the Gospel of Luke and 7 lines for the
                           Gospel of Mark; 1-3 lines in the incipit of all the chapters; some
                           paragraph beginnings (1-3 lines) and some other passages; incipit (one
                           line) of some minor texts within the Introduction and the
                           Postscript;
 parts of the Canon tables; Ethiopic numerals indicating
                           the “tituli”; elements of the punctuation signs.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
