               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0131DMB">Bäʿatti Qǝddus Mikāʾel / DMB</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1889" notAfter="1913">Additio 1 mentions King Mǝnilǝk (r.
                        1889-1913) and Metropolitan Ṗeṭros (in tenure 1881-1917).
 Additio 1
                        refers to the year of Mark the Evangelist. This means that the Ms. could
                        have been written in years 1889/90, 1897/98, 1905/6 or 1912/13(cp. ChChron
                        219).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Commissioned by Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer, according to Additione 1
                     and 2.
 Besides, Additio 1 and 2 mentions names of other individuals
                     (probably his relatives): Walda Sǝmʿon, Walatta Mikāʾel, ʿAmda Mikāʾel, Mazgaba
                     Śǝllāse, Walda Yoḥannǝs, Takla Hāymānot, Walatta Yoḥannǝs, Walatta Giyorgis,
                     ʾAmata ʾIyasus, Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ, Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ, Walatta Ṣādǝqān,
                     Walatta Madḫǝn.
 Some of these names are also mentioned in the supplication
                     formulas, at the end of several sub-sections (s., e.g., <locus target="#7va">7va</locus>, 16va), added in a different hand.</provenance>
               </history>
